HEADWORD: Tectibranchiate
<hw>Tec`ti*bran"chi*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tectus</ets> (p. p. of <ets>tegere</ets> to cover) + E.
<ets>branchiate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the gills
covered by the mantle; of or pertaining to the Tectibranchiata.</def> --
